<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 4:57PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Catawba, southeastern
Alexander, western Lincoln, northern Iredell and north central
Cleveland Counties through 530 PM EDT...
At 457 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 5 miles east of Taylorsville to 13 miles west
of Lincolnton. Movement was east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Statesville, Newton, Lincolnton, Hickory, St. Stephens, Conover,
Maiden, Stony Point, Claremont and Belwood.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
